\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720 In some sense, learning math is kind of like exercising. There are now many different kinds of exercise machines that can help you focus on different muscle groups: treadmill, elliptical machine, stationary bike, stair master, and each also has many variations and different programs. However, regardless of which software or exercise machine you use, the most important thing is to build a solid foundation. If you just like paper and pencil or jogging outside, that's perfectly fine. I have seen too many points lost by former students due to simple mistakes. So please make sure that you completely understand one step before moving on to the next one. This may takes more time at the beginning, but the effort will definitely pay off.\par

