\pard\nowidctlpar I think in China nowadays they do read from top to bottom and from left to right just like in US. But in some antique stores where you may find some copies of old books, you can see that those books are columnwise and right to left. Yes, it certainly takes some getting used to, but after some practice you'll see that a new order is not harder than the old one. The point is that you have to practice very slowly and persistently at the beginning. If I'm in a hurry to solve a math problem, I tend to make many small mistakes including missing the -sign in front of the numerals. That's why I don't like in class exams. So I guess the solution is: don't be in a hurry, always starts early and read and solve each problem very carefully.\par
