\pard\nowidctlpar Thanks for sharing your positive experience, Colleen, I can't agree with you more.  In my opinion, mathematics is very much alike some physical skills, for example swimming.  After enough practice, everyone can be reasonably good at math/swimming.  Of course most people won't be able to go to the Olympics no matter how hard they practice, similarly only a few highly gifted ones can become first-class mathematicians. But we're not talking about that level of skills. We're talking about mastering the course material and being able to solve most problems correctly/swimming a few laps at ease. Math is challenging, but not much harder than water. All it takes is to practice carefully and consistently.\par
